---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SteganographyView from '../../components/tools/Steganography.svelte';
---

<Layout 
  title="Steganography â€” Covert Communication"
  description="Hide secret messages inside regular image files. Advanced LSB (Least Significant Bit) encoding combined with AES-256 encryption."
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-5 py-12 md:py-20 text-center">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-black italic tracking-tighter mb-4">Stegano<span class="text-emerald-500">graphy.</span></h1>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed max-w-xl mx-auto font-medium">
        Hide your secrets in plain sight. This tool injects encrypted data into the least significant bits of image pixels.
        To the naked eye, the image remains unchanged.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card p-4 md:p-10">
      <SteganographyView client:load />
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 text-left bg-zinc-50 dark:bg-zinc-900/50 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-500 mb-3">Technical Overview</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-xs text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 font-medium leading-relaxed">
            <p>
                <strong class="text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-200">1. Hybrid Security:</strong> Your message is first encrypted using AES-256-GCM. 
                Even if someone detects the hidden bits, they cannot read them without your password.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong class="text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-200">2. LSB Encoding:</strong> We use the 3 least significant bits of the RGB channels. 
                This provides high capacity while keeping the visual variance below human perception.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
